3:T82a,You are a customer support specialist for [BRAND NAME], a [PRODUCT TYPE]
brand. Your tone is warm, direct, and knowledgeable — like a helpful friend
who genuinely knows the products, not a scripted support bot.

You will receive a JSON object containing:
- The customer's support ticket text
- Their order history (from Shopify)
- Relevant product information
- Their customer tier (first-time, repeat, VIP)

Your task: write a complete, personalized support reply that fully resolves
the customer's issue.

TONE GUIDELINES:
- First-time customers: warm and welcoming, acknowledge it's their first order
- Repeat customers: familiar, reference their purchase history if relevant
- VIP (3+ orders): treat them like a brand insider

RESPONSE STRUCTURE:
1. Address them by first name
2. Acknowledge their specific situation in one sentence (don't paraphrase
   their whole message back to them)
3. Answer or resolve their question/issue directly
4. If order-related: include specific tracking or status details from the data
5. One optional closing line — a relevant tip, or a genuine sign-off

HARD RULES:
- Never make up order details, tracking numbers, or product information
  not present in the data
- Never promise a specific delivery date unless you have confirmed data
- Never offer a refund or credit — those are Tier 2/3 decisions
- If the data is insufficient to answer fully, say so directly and tell
  them what to do next (reply with X, or email Y@brand.com)
- Do not use: "I hope this helps", "Please don't hesitate", "Feel free to",
  "Certainly!", "Absolutely!", or any hollow affirmations
- Keep replies under 150 words unless the complexity genuinely requires more
- No sign-off signatures — the email footer handles that

ESCALATION — do not respond, flag immediately if you detect:
- Any mention of an allergic reaction, rash, hives, or medical symptom
- Legal language: "lawyer", "sue", "BBB", "FTC", "dispute", "chargeback"
- Any claim of physical harm
- Refund requests over $[THRESHOLD]
- The words "journalist", "article", "review", or press-related context0:["cEhtJqdwv2musQR5XQayr",[[["",{"children":["issues",{"children":["customer-service-ai-ecommerce",{"children":["__PAGE__",{}]}]}]},"$undefined","$undefined",true],["",{"children":["issues",{"children":["customer-service-ai-ecommerce",{"children":["__PAGE__",{},["$L1",["$","main",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0a]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-6 py-4","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/","className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c] hover:text-[#d4b660] transition-colors","children":"← Operators Brief"}],["$","a",null,{"href":"/#signup","className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-widest uppercase bg-[#c9a84c] text-[#0a0a0a] px-4 py-2 hover:bg-[#d4b660] transition-colors","children":"Get All 52 Issues — $15/mo"}]]}]}],["$","article",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 mb-8","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"Deep Dive"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"w-1 h-1 bg-[#2a2a2a] rounded-full"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550]","children":"Free Issue"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"w-1 h-1 bg-[#2a2a2a] rounded-full"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550]","children":"E-Commerce / DTC"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"w-1 h-1 bg-[#2a2a2a] rounded-full"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550]","children":"10-min read"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-[32px] md:text-[44px] font-light leading-[1.1] tracking-tight text-[#f0ede8] mb-5","children":"How a 2-Person DTC Brand Cut Support Costs by 67% Without Losing Customers"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[18px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-12 border-l-2 border-[#c9a84c] pl-5","children":"A two-person skincare brand was spending $11,000/month on a 3-person support team to handle 1,200 tickets. Here's the Gorgias + Claude API workflow that resolved 74% of those tickets automatically — while CSAT went up."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"w-full h-px bg-[#1e1e1e] mb-12"}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"01"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#5a5550]","children":"The Problem"}]]}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-light text-[#f0ede8] mb-5 leading-snug","children":"1,200 tickets/month. 3 support agents. $11K/month. And CSAT still at 3.9."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"Evergreen Skin Co. is a bootstrapped skincare brand doing $2.1M ARR with two founders and a small remote team. Their Shopify store generates 1,200 support tickets a month — about 40 a day. To handle that volume, they had three part-time support agents totaling $11,200/month in labor."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"The bigger problem: their CSAT sat at 3.9/5. Not because the agents were bad — they weren't. It was because 78% of tickets were asking the same 11 questions: Where's my order? Can I exchange this shade? What's in this serum? How do I apply the moisturizer with my retinol? The agents were answering these on a loop, getting bored, and slipping on response consistency."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"The founders were also fielding escalations: refund requests, ingredient allergy concerns, and influencer partnership DMs — all in the same inbox. No routing, no prioritization, no triage."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-[#0d0d0d] border border-[#1e1e1e] p-5 my-8","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] font-mono text-[#5a5550] mb-2 uppercase tracking-wider","children":"The ticket breakdown:"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#f0ede8]","children":["Of 1,200 monthly tickets: 936 (78%) were FAQ-type questions answerable without human judgment.",["$","br",null,{}],"264 (22%) needed real human involvement: refunds, complaints, complex issues.",["$","br",null,{}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-[#c9a84c]","children":"$$11K/month spent handling tickets that didn't require human agents."}]]}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"02"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#5a5550]","children":"The Workflow"}]]}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-light text-[#f0ede8] mb-5 leading-snug","children":"The 3-tier resolution system"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-8","children":"They built this inside Gorgias using native automations + Claude API via webhook. No custom code required for the core flow. Total setup time: 11 days. One founder handled the Gorgias configuration; a Zapier-connected Claude API integration handled the response generation."}],[["$","div","0",{"className":"mb-6 border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Tier 1"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Gorgias Rules + Claude API"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"px-5 py-4","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[15px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8] mb-3","children":"Instant auto-resolution — FAQ responses"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"Incoming tickets are classified by Gorgias's built-in intent detection. Tickets tagged as order-status, product-info, ingredients, usage-instructions, or shipping-timeline are passed immediately to Claude with the customer's order data (pulled from Shopify via Gorgias integration) and the full product knowledge base. Claude generates a personalized response. The response is sent automatically; the ticket is closed. No human ever sees it unless the customer replies unhappy. Tier 1 handles 74% of all tickets."}]]}]]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"mb-6 border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Tier 2"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Gorgias + Claude API + agent queue"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"px-5 py-4","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[15px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8] mb-3","children":"Drafted response — human review before send"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"Tickets tagged as exchange-request, complaint, or subscription-issue are sent to Claude for a draft response with recommended action. Claude drafts the reply and flags it: \"Recommended: approve exchange for shade mismatch, standard policy applies.\" An agent reviews the draft in 30–60 seconds, edits if needed, and sends with one click. This tier handles 18% of tickets. Agent time per ticket: 45 seconds vs. 6 minutes previously."}]]}]]}],["$","div","2",{"className":"mb-6 border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Tier 3"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Gorgias priority tags + Slack alert"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"px-5 py-4","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[15px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8] mb-3","children":"Direct escalation — founders only"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"Tickets matching any escalation trigger (see Section 04) bypass Claude entirely and surface immediately in a dedicated Slack channel with full ticket context. These are refunds over $150, allergy reports, any mention of a medical term or adverse reaction, legal language, media or press inquiries, and influencer DMs. Founders respond within 2 hours. This tier is 8% of tickets. No SLA misses since implementation."}]]}]]}]]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"03"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#5a5550]","children":"Resolution Rate Benchmarks"}]]}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-light text-[#f0ede8] mb-5 leading-snug","children":"Industry benchmarks and where this brand landed"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-6","children":"DTC support benchmarks for context — and where Evergreen landed 90 days post-implementation:"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"overflow-x-auto mb-8","children":["$","table",null,{"className":"w-full border border-[#1e1e1e] text-[13px]","children":[["$","thead",null,{"children":["$","tr",null